## Leeds sectors I work with

My client base in Leeds and West Yorkshire spans several of the city's strongest industries.

**Financial services** — Leeds is home to over 30 banks and building societies, plus hundreds of fintech companies, IFAs, and financial planning firms. I understand the compliance sensitivities and E-E-A-T requirements that make financial services SEO particularly demanding.

**Legal** — With over 100 law firms in the city centre alone, the legal market in Leeds is fiercely competitive online. I help solicitors and legal practices build topical authority in their practice areas while maintaining the professional tone their clients expect.

**Digital and technology** — The tech sector around Leeds Dock and the South Bank development is booming. For SaaS companies, digital agencies, and tech startups, I build SEO strategies that drive qualified demo requests and trial signups rather than vanity traffic.

**Healthcare** — From private clinics to NHS-adjacent services, healthcare SEO requires careful attention to YMYL standards and E-E-A-T signals. I build authority structures that satisfy both Google's quality raters and patients searching for trustworthy providers.

**Education** — Training providers, tutoring services, and edtech companies in Leeds benefit from long-tail content strategies that capture students and parents at every stage of the decision journey.

**Retail and ecommerce** — Whether you're running a Leeds-based ecommerce operation or a brick-and-mortar retailer with an online presence, I optimise product visibility, category architecture, and commercial landing pages for maximum revenue impact.

## How we work together

I'm based in the UK and work remotely with all my clients. For Leeds businesses, this means you get the same responsiveness and strategic depth as a local consultant without paying for my commute.

Every engagement starts with a discovery call where I learn about your business, your goals, and your current search performance. From there, I produce a detailed audit and strategy document outlining exactly what needs to happen and in what order.

Communication happens through regular video calls, shared dashboards, and a direct line to me — no ticketing systems or waiting for account managers to relay messages. You'll always know what's being worked on, what's been completed, and what's coming next.

For ongoing retainers, I provide monthly reporting that focuses on commercial metrics — revenue, leads, and conversions — not just rankings and traffic numbers.

## Pricing for Leeds SEO consulting

I offer flexible engagement models to suit different business sizes and needs. For a detailed breakdown of what to expect, read my guide on [how much does SEO cost](/services/how-much-does-seo-cost/).

**One-off audits** start from £750 and include a comprehensive technical and content review with prioritised recommendations.

**Monthly retainers** typically range from £1,000 to £3,000 depending on scope, covering ongoing strategy, implementation, and reporting.

**Project-based work** is available for specific initiatives like site migrations, content overhauls, or new site launches.

Every engagement begins with that free consultation — no obligation, no hard sell.

